name: Tina's Big Burrito Red Hot Beef Burrito, 16 oz Plastic Film, 1 Count (Frozen)
shortDescription: Tina's Burritos The Burrito Lover's Burritos. Every minute approximately 694 people eat a Tina's Burrito! We bake up a million budget friendly burritos in our Los Angeles, CA factory daily and serve them to hungry burrito lovers who appreciate great taste, convenience, and quick meals full of nutritious ingredients. All of our products are slow cooked in large kettles, so the spices blend together for a flavor profile that is considered to be the best tasting frozen burrito on grocers' shelves. Then we flash freeze the burritos for freshness. Since Tina's Burritos are frozen, we do not need to use any artificial flavors or preservatives. Many customers write in and say they have been "addicted" to Tina's frozen burritos since 1980 when we first started making them. Others write in and say they started buying our products with food stamps because it was all they could afford, but now they buy Tina's Burritos with money in the bank. We are very proud to be able to produce a high quality product that helps eliminate food insecurity in America and save our customers time and money that can be put towards advancing their own lives. WHAT ARE TINA'S VALUES? CONSISTENCY We taste test our products every week and invite our new and regular customers to be a part of the "Take the Tina's Taste Test Challenge" We use that feedback to make our products the best that they can be. CHOICE We are the burrito company that champions choice because we realize that different people have different needs. We have over 60 burrito varieties to choose from to satisfy your unique lifestyle and tastes preferences. QUALITY We source our products directly from farms and the original manufacturers to streamline production, implement quality control to ensure a high-level product at a low cost. CREATIVITY We listen to the feedback from our customers and design products and packaging based on their needs not ours. COMFORT We are committed to providing customers with the most accurate and up to date information on our products so they can easily find Tina's Burritos using the technology of their choice. Tina's is the frozen burrito manufacturer that has served over 2 Billion Burritos to happy customers since their founding over 40 years ago! We know how to roll a burrito! Visit our website for frozen burrito recipe ideas! Tina's Beef & Bean Burritos are loved by all people in just about every demographic. Tina's crosses the divide because we all need a little comfort food at some point. Having something that is easy to cook, affordable but high value, and superior in taste in the freezer helps folks adjust to whatever life can throw at them. Try Tina's Burritos at Walmart! #WeServeTheMasses

Fred has a little more help these days, but his family's commitment to authentic Mexican spices, high-quality ingredients, and satisfying family recipes remains unchanged. The Puff Story: Back in 1927, when prohibition was dragging along, family man and Chicago entrepreneur, Elisha Shabaz made no small plans when creating his food company. He began with recipe's so incredibly fun that an entire city could momentarily forget its troubles. Thankfully, big thinking led to the invention of The Original Pizza Puff. The plan was to hand-fold each Puff, using ingredients like real flour tortillas, home-style sauces, vegetables, quality meats, cheeses, and spices. All of these ingredients coming together on a deliciousness scale that is worthy of a strong and proud city. Often imitated by larger food companies, but never duplicated, the Puff is still hand-folded, using quality ingredients, by a real family. Here at Iltaco we aspire to continuing the Puff legacy by making great tasting food for real people. So, if you love the Puff as much as we love making them, then please let us know. Go forth, enjoy our invention, and share the goodness through social interaction so that we may bring new smiles to new faces across this great nation. Warmest regards, - The Italco Family. Whether you have to feed a whole house or just need a quick start lunch for the kids, El Monterey taquitos are perfect for every occasion. El Monterey Taquitos – America's #1 Frozen Mexican Company Since 1964 Fred Ruiz began El Monterey in 1964 crouched over a stand mixer and a book of his mother's traditional Mexican recipes. Back then, Fred stored his frozen taquitos and frozen appetizers in a chest freezer before sending them off for sale with his father, Louis. Fred may have several thousand more hands helping them out these days but his family's commitment to high-quality ingredients and traditional Mexican flavor remains the same. As his mother always said, “Promise you'll always prepare foods you would be proud to serve your family and friends at home.” Of course, moms always know best! Bigger! Bolder! Chicken and Monterey Jack Cheese Taquitos are Ready to Enjoy in Minutes Boxed taquitos by El Monterey are frozen for your convenience and take only a few minutes to prepare – both in the oven and microwave. The 8-count pack is perfect for making a meal or pulling a few out for quick snack food. Stock your freezer with El Monterey taquitos for a satisfying and delicious meal anytime, anywhere! Conventional Oven Directions: Preheat your oven to 400º F Place 4 frozen taquitos on a baking sheet lined with parchment paper Bake uncovered for 15 minutes Don't dig in just yet! Let them cool for at least 1 minute Microwave Directions (1,100 watts): Place 2 taquitos on a microwave-safe plate Cook on high for 1 minute and 30 seconds Allow them to cool for at least 1 minute before biting into the cheesy goodness Safe Handling Instructions: For food safety and quality, internal product temperature must reach 161° F. Since ovens and microwaves vary, cooking times may require adjusting. Caution: Product may be extremely hot. Bigger! Bolder! Chicken and Monterey Jack Cheese Taquitos – and Much More – Bursting with Flavor from Authentic Mexican Spices Taste the Ruiz family tradition today with El Monterey Bigger! Bolder! The Puff Story: Back in 1927, when prohibition was dragging along, family man and Chicago entrepreneur, Elisha Shabaz made no small plans when creating his food company. He began with recipe's so incredibly fun that an entire city could momentarily forget its troubles. Thankfully, big thinking led to the invention of The Original Pizza Puff. The plan was to hand-fold each Puff, using ingredients like real flour tortillas, home-style sauces, vegetables, quality meats, cheeses, and spices. All of these ingredients coming together on a deliciousness scale that is worthy of a strong and proud city. Often imitated by larger food companies, but never duplicated, the Puff is still hand-folded, using quality ingredients, by a real family. Here at Iltaco we aspire to continuing the Puff legacy by making great tasting food for real people. So, if you love the Puff as much as we love making them, then please let us know. Go forth, enjoy our invention, and share the goodness through social interaction so that we may bring new smiles to new faces across this great nation. Warmest regards, - The Italco Family. Visit us (at) iltaco.com. Like us on: Twitter; Facebook; Instagram.

name: Delicious Bite Delicious Bite Tequenos, 16 ea
shortDescription: Tequenos 16 tequenos [12 oz (340 g)] Authentic Venezuelan style. Artisan dough filled with Queso Blanco. Queso Blanco - a uniquely Hispanic white cheese - delightfully mild, soft & creamy when heated. Hand rolled gourmet artisan dough, buttery & flavorful, never greasy. Both children & adults will love this traditional Venezuelan dish. We make each bite a special moment! Excellent source of calcium. No trans fat. Our Tequenos are made only in small continuous batches and are hand rolled - the only way to maintain their authentic flavor and unique texture. The gourmet artisan dough used to wrap the delightful Hispanic Queso Blanco is based upon principles of the ancient art of dough making. We've taken the time so you don't have to. Very fast and easy to prepare, just fry them and serve them with a surprisingly wide variety of dipping sauces. Try them alone or with ketchup, hot sauces, mayonnaise, mustards, Asian sauces, and salsas. We at Delicious Bite guarantee our Tequenos will make each bite a special moment. VPA preferred. Registered Pennsylvania Department of Agriculture. Keep frozen. Original Recipe Cooking Method: Pan Fry: Preheat 1/2 inch of vegetable oil (approx. 1 cup of vegetable oil) in a medium size skillet under medium heat. Once oil begins to ripple, place frozen Tequenos (approx. 7 to 8 at a time), for 3 to 4 minutes, until golden brown on both sides. Remove the Tequenos from the skillet using a slotted spoon, drain on absorbent paper, and let stand for 3 minutes before serving. Conventional Oven: Preheat oven to 450 F. Arrange frozen Tequenos in single layer on baking sheet so Tequenos are not touching. Turn oven down to 425 degrees F. Bake 12 minutes on middle oven rack. For best results, turn Tequenos over after 6 minutes. Let stand for 3 minutes before serving. Deep Fry: Preheat oil 350 degrees F. Fry frozen Tequenos for 3 to 4 minutes. Drain on absorbent paper, and let stand for 3 minutes before serving. Precautions: Do not leave pan unattended while heating. Add frozen Tequenos to hot oil carefully as ice crystals on frozen food can cause oil to spatter. Allergen: contains wheat, milk, soy, egg. 16 tequenos [12 oz (340 g)] West Chester, PA 19380

Many customers write in and say they have been "addicted" to Tina’s frozen burritos since 1980 when we first started making them. Others write in and say they started buying our products with food stamps because it was all they could afford, but now they buy Tina's Burritos with money in the bank. We are very proud to be able to produce a high quality product that helps eliminate food insecurity in America and save our customers time and money that can be put towards advancing their own lives. WHAT ARE TINA’S VALUES? CONSISTENCY We taste test our products every week and invite our customers to be a part of the “Take the Tina’s Taste Test Challenge” at tinasburritos.com. We use that feedback to make our products the best that they can be. CHOICE We are the burrito company that champions choice because we realize that different people have different needs. We have over 60 burrito varieties to choose from to satisfy your unique lifestyle and tastes preferences. QUALITY We source our products directly from farms and the original manufacturers to streamline production, implement quality control to ensure a high-level product at a low cost. CREATIVITY We listen to the feedback from our customers and design products and packaging based on their needs not ours. COMFORT We are committed to providing customers with the most accurate and up to date information on our products so they can easily find Tina’s Burritos using the technology of their choice. Tina’s is the frozen burrito manufacturer that has served over 2 Billion Burritos to happy customers since their founding over 40 years ago! We know how to roll a burrito! Visit our website at tinasburritos.com for frozen burrito recipe ideas! Tina’s Beef & Bean Green Chili Burritos are loved by all people in just about every demographic. Tina’s crosses the divide because we all need a little comfort food at some point. Having something that is easy to cook, affordable but high value, and superior in taste in the freezer helps folks adjust to whatever life can throw at them. Try Tina’s Burritos at Walmart! #WeServeTheMasses

shortDescription: Tina’s Burritos, Red Chili & Cheese Burritos, 32 oz, 8 Count Pack The Burrito Lover’s Burritos. Every minute approximately 694 people eat a Tina’s Burrito! We bake up a million budget friendly burritos in our Los Angeles, CA factory daily and serve them to hungry burrito lovers who appreciate great taste, convenience, and quick meals filled with nutritious ingredients. All of our products are slow cooked in large kettles, so the spices blend together for a flavor profile that is considered to be the best tasting frozen burrito on grocers’ shelves. Then we flash freeze the burritos for freshness. Since Tina’s Burritos are frozen, we do not need to use any artificial flavors or preservatives. Many customers write in and say they have been "addicted" to Tina’s frozen burritos since 1980 when we first started making them. Others write in and say they started buying our products with food stamps because it was all they could afford, but now they buy Tina's Burritos with money in the bank. We are very proud to be able to produce a high quality product that helps eliminate food insecurity in America and save our customers time and money that can be put towards advancing their own lives. WHAT ARE TINA’S VALUES? CONSISTENCY We taste test our products every week and invite our customers to be a part of the “Take the Tina’s Taste Test Challenge” . We use that feedback to make our products the best that they can be. CHOICE We are the burrito company that champions choice because we realize that different people have different needs. name: Tina's Red Hot Beef Burritos Value Pack, 56 oz, Carton, 14 Count (Frozen)
shortDescription: Tina's Red Hot Beef Burritos Value Pack, 56 oz, Carton, 14 Count (Frozen) The Burrito Lover's Burritos. Every minute approximately 694 people eat a Tina's Burrito! We bake up a million hardy but budget friendly burritos in our Los Angeles, CA factory daily and serve them to hungry burrito lovers who appreciate great taste, convenience, and quick meals full of nutritious ingredients. All of our products are slow cooked in large kettles, so the spices blend together for a flavor profile that is considered to be the best tasting frozen burrito on grocers? shelves. Then we flash freeze the burritos for freshness. Since Tina's Burritos are frozen, we do not need to use any artificial flavors or preservatives. Many customers write in and say they have been "addicted" to Tina's frozen burritos since 1980 when we first started making them. Others write in and say they started buying our products with food stamps because it was all they could afford, but now they buy Tina's Burritos with money in the bank. We are very proud to be able to produce a high-quality product that helps eliminate food insecurity in America and save our customers time and money that can be put towards advancing their own lives.
